body:
The `ClusterConnection::pending_requests` is the queue of requests which are not yet responded as result of `ClusterConnection::read` calls.
Occasionally it might have multiple entires in different states like:
1. Unfulfilled request (requested from node 0);
2. Fulfilled request (responded by node 1);
3. Fulfilled request (responded by node 2);

Currently calls to `ClusterConnection::read` will be "head of line" blocked until request on top of the queue is fulfilled. So fulfilling request on top of the queue might unblock multiple queued requests. The response to completed requests on top of the queue should not be blocked with socket read operation.

Added test which shows conditions when `ClusterConnection::read` is stuck.
The conditions are the following:
1. `ClusterConnection` sent cmd1 and cmd2 commands to node1 & node2;
2. `ClusterConnection` received responses first from node2 and then from node1;
3. `ClusterConnection::read` is completed with the response to cmd2, but does not respond with result to cmd1 (until event from any of standalone connections, which could never happen no more commands is sent over connection)
